Titolo: Bristles (video game)

Anno: 1983

Descrizione: Bristles is a video game written by Fernando Herrera for the Atari 8-bit family and published by the company he cofounded, First Star Software, in 1983. It was ported to the Commodore 64, ZX Spectrum, and Exidy's Max-A-Flex arcade system. In Bristles, the player uses ladders and elevators to move Peter the Painter through a cutaway view of a house to paint all the walls.